<h4 id="Topic">Thinking of a topic:</h4>
<p>Any article that is pitched should be specifically made for a teenage audience. This means it addresses a topic, experience, and/or problem that is felt by, or of interest to, some or most teens. It is not enough for the article to be of interest to some teens just because the topic has such a broad audience already (see diagram).</p>
<%= image_tag("specificity_diagram.png", class: "image_fit_scrn") %>
<p>It can be helpful to keep some notes on your phone to jot down ideas for article topics. If you are currently in, or just graduated, high school, think about your daily life and the things that you are struggling with. What excites you? What scares you? What would you love to learn more about?
  Chances are your daily life is made up of experiences similar to those of lots of other teens your age. What you wonder about, what sparks your curiosity, what worries you, what stresses you out, are common experiences and should be drawn upon when thinking of new topics. Keep in mind that any article topic you pitch should fall in one of these categories:</p>

